Commands:
    add_ignoremeasures:
      
    add_ignoremeasures command is used to create an instance of ignore measure object. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    analyze_chain_diagnosability:
      
    analyze_chain_diagnosability is used to select the best test sequences for 
    performing scan chain diagnostics.

    analyze_compression_testpoints:
      
    analyze_compression_testpoints identifies testpoints to help reduce pattern count 
    when running ATPG using a testmode that uses compression technology.

    analyze_deterministic_faults:
      
    analyze_deterministic_faults provides tools for analyzing the deterministic
    testability of faults. With this command you can justify values on pins, 
    analyze sources preventing fault activation/propagation, or trace inactive faults. 

    analyze_deterministic_testpoints:
      
    analyze_deterministic_testpoints is used to create a testpoint insertion file 
    for untested faults given an input experiment.  INEXPERIMENT is required.  
    If running with option inactive=yes/no, fault=nn, or tgfaultlist=infilename INEXPERIMENT is not required. 

    analyze_diagnostics_db:
      
    analyze_diagnostics_db is used for querying the database created using 'prepare_diagnostics_db' 
    command. The set of queries is provided through input query file. 

    analyze_embedded_test:
      
     analyze_embedded_test is used to perform diagnostic, repair or production 
     analysis for memory built-in self test (MBIST) patterns. 

    analyze_failset:
      
    analyze_failset performs analysis and generates reports for a failset.

    analyze_hotspots:
      
    analyze_hotspots is used to analyze one or more hotspot files and filter out 
    required information into a seperate hotspot file. This command currently supports 
    hotspot files in HIF format. 

    analyze_lbist_testpoints:
      
    analyze_lbist_testpoints analyzes faults and recommends test points that
    can be inserted to improve random pattern testability.  This is intended 
    for logic that is to be tested with LBIST (or WRPT).

    analyze_paths:
      
    analyze_paths command is used for analysis of paths tested using create_path_delay_tests command. 

    analyze_testability:
      
    analyze_testability analyzes faults for testability with deterministic 
    test generation techniques. Reasons for untestable faults are given. 

    analyze_vectors:
      
    analyze_vectors provides special simulation techniques for analyzing 
    the effectiveness/accuracy/completeness of test vectors. 

    analyze_volume_trends:
      
    analyze_volume_trends is used to upload the volume files, created by 
    diagnose_volume_failures, into the volume diagnostics database and to report 
    various trends in failure and callout data in the volume diagnostics database.

    build_alternate_faultmodel:
      
    build_alternate_faultmodel is used to build a fault model that is 
    different than the normal fault model.  This is typically used for 
    diagnostics, but can be used for test generation/simulation as well 

    build_alternate_faultmodel_ht:
      
    build_alternate_faultmodel_ht is used to build alternate fault models 
    for hierarchical test designs. In addition to building the alternate 
    fault model for the top level chip logic, any needed alternate fault 
    models for out-of-context core processing are built. This is useful for 
    facilitating diagnostics when these fault models are not readily available.

    build_boundary_model:
      
    build_boundary_model is used to create a boundary model for a chip or core.
    The resulting boundary model will be used as input for building the logic model
    for the next level of structure, either a MCM or SOC.
    create_interconnect_tests is used for creating ATPG patterns for a MCM.
    create_logic_tests is used for creating ATPG patterns for a SOC.

    build_bridge_faultmodel:
      
    build_bridge_faultmodel is used to build a bridge fault model by generating 
    the probable bridge candidates using the physical design information. This is 
    typically used for diagnostics, but can be used for test generation/simulation 
    as well. 

    build_chip_hier_testmode:
      
    build_chip_hier_testmode is used to define a testmode which will
    be used for migrating tests for embedded cores where the tests have
    been generated at the core level "out of context."  It recognizes
    configuration register latches by the ET_HIERTEST_CONFIG property, and
    creates the mode initialization sequence.  Its other primary job is to
    recognize any chip level PLLs, and program and lock them via the mode
    initialization sequence.  When chip-level PLLs exist, it must also modify
    the testmode definition file.  When at-speed tests are being migrated,
    it processes information that is intended to be sent to Manufacturing
    via specal "keyed data" setup sequence definitions.  After building
    the input files, it invokes the build_core_migration_testmode command.

    build_core_migration_model:
      
    build_core_migration_model is used to create an out-of-context core migration
    model for migration of core ATPG patterns to the SOC.
    The resulting core migration model will be used as input for building the 
    logic model of the SOC.

    build_core_migration_testmode:
      
    build_core_migration_testmode is used to build test modes for the chip-level 
    migration of core test patterns. 

    build_diagreturn_sequence:
      
    build_diagreturn_sequence is used to create the diagnostic observe and 
    diagnostic return sequence definitions. These sequence definitions are 
    included in a file, along with any user-specified sequences (such as 
    custom mode initialization or scan sequences), and used as input to 
    the build_testmode command. 

    build_extest_assignfile:
      
    build_extest_assignfile creates assignfiles for Genus CHIP generated assignfile with the 
    appropriate CORE generated assignfile. This assignfile can be used when CHIP testmodes 
    are created with build_testmode for CHIP ATPG pattern generation.

    build_faultmodel:
      
    build_faultmodel is used to build the fault model for the device 
    under test.

    build_flatmodel:
      
    build_flatmodel is used to create the flatModel from the hierModel. 
    It is normally run as part of build_model. 

    build_internal_domains_testmode:
      
    build_internal_domains_testmode is used to define a testmode for a device
    with special clock control macros.  It defines cutpoints and PPIs based 
    on model attributes which identify the clock control registers, and point 
    to programming files which describe the operation of these registers. 
    This information is used to enhance the modedef and seqdef files before 
    invoking build_testmode.

    build_library_model:
      
    build_library_model is used to build a binary technology library model. 

    build_manufacturing_interface:
      
    build_manufacturing_interface is used to create a file that contains
    all the files that can be used by manufacturing test or diagnostics.

    build_memory_model:
      
    build_memory_model assists in the creation of memory models for use with 
    Modus ATPG.

    build_model:
      
    build_model builds the logic model files from the input netlist
    and library cell descriptions.

    build_opcg_testmode:
      
    build_opcg_testmode is used to define an at-speed testmode for a device
    with on-product clock generation (OPCG).  It defines cutpoints and PPIs 
    based on model attributes which identify PLL and clock-generation control
    registers, and point to programming files which describe the operation of 
    these registers. This information is used to enhance the modedef and seqdef
    files before invoking build_testmode.

    build_sdtsnt_objectives:
      
    build_sdtsnt_objectives is used to create the set of stuck driver test 
    and/or shorted nets test objectives to be targetted for IOWRAP or 
    interconnect tests. 

    build_testmode:
      
    build_testmode is used to build test modes which define the scan structure
    and active logic for testing. 

    build_top_shell:
      
    build_top_shell is used to build design-for-test structures such as 
    boundary scan, on-product MISR, or LBIST and connect them to the   
    core design logic. 

    characterize_cellaware_defects:
      
  characterize_cellaware_defects is used in the cell aware fault modeling flow to characterize 
  extracted candidate defects in standard digital library cells for subsequent fault modeling. 

    cdnshelp:
      
    cdnshelp is used to access the Cadence documentation. It is entered without
    any options. This is the same as the GUI Help pulldown List of Books. 

    check_flow:
      
    check_flow command is used to perform syntax checking on the flow. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    commit_faultstatus:
      
  commit_faultstatus is used to commit fault status to an alternate fault model from
  an input experiment derived from committed tests.  This is similar to committing tests
  however in this case, the associated tests have already been committed.  Committing
  fault status propagates it to all test modes and this optimizes the ATPG flow by realizing
  test coverage across test modes (for faults active in multiple test modes).  Thus if a fault
  is active in multiple test modes and is tested in a test mode, committing its fault status
  avoids the need to target it in any other test mode where it is active.

    commit_tests:
      
    commit_tests is used to accumulate the vectors and fault coverage from an 
    experiment into the master test data for the test mode. 

    compact_vectors:
      
    compact_vectors is used to remove vectors that don't meet specified 
    criteria.  It can also be used to sort the vectors. 

    convert_comp_to_fullscan:
      
    convert_comp_to_fullscan is used to convert COMPRESSION patterns produced by ATPG for
    compression parts to FULLSCAN patterns to help with diagnostics.

    convert_cpp_to_failures:
      
  convert_cpp_to_failures command converts Chip-Pad-Pattern format fail data in Modus Diagnostics to tester fail data format. 

    convert_failures_to_cpp:
      
    Converts tester fail data format to Chip-Pad-Pattern format fail data 
    for Modus Diagnostics. 

    convert_lbist_failures:
      
    convert_lbist_failures is used to read fail data generated from patterns 
    created for LBIST designs and write a failure file which can be read 
    and diagnosed using diagnose_failures.

    convert_multiscan_failures:
      
    convert_multiscan_failures is used to read fail data generated from patterns 
    containing Multiple Scan Sections and write a failure file which can be read 
    and diagnosed using diagnose_failures.

    convert_opmisr_to_xor:
      
    convert_opmisr_to_xor is used to convert OPMISR patterns produced by ATPG for
    compression parts to XOR patterns to help with diagnostics.

    convert_signatures:
      
    convert_signatures reads in a TBDbin experiment and a user supplied MOS pin setting file. 
    It creates a set of Composite_MISR_Signature events from the Product_MISR_Signature 
    and the MOS Pin States supplied within the MOS file.  The new  Composite_MISR_Signature  
    events within the output experiment are used  by write_vectors to view specifically selected MISRs.    

    convert_smartscan_failures:
      
    convert_smartscan_failures is used to convert failures obtained from SmartScan 
    patterns on the tester to their respective XOR compression patterns. The 
    converted failures and the XOR compression experiment are used as input 
    to diagnose_failures.

    convert_stil_to_modedef:
      
    convert_stil_to_modedef reads a stil file and generates ASSIGN and 
    seqdef files which are used to build a testmode. 

    convert_vectors_for_macro_tests:
      
    convert_vectors_for_macro_tests is used to convert vectors for an IP macro 
    to the format required for creating macro tests for the SoC when the macro 
    is embedded in another device. 

    convert_vectors_to_multiscan:
      
    convert_vectors_to_multiscan is used to convert patterns produced by ATPG for 
    multiple partitions to patterns that are applied one partition at a time. 

    convert_vectors_to_smartscan:
      
    convert_vectors_to_smartscan is used to convert the parallel patterns produced by
    ATPG for compression parts to serial patterns required by the SmartScan architecture.

    convert_vectors_to_stored_pattern:
      
    convert_vectors_to_stored_pattern is used to convert signature-based test 
    vectors to stored pattern format. 

    copy_row_faultstatus:
      
    copy_row_faultstatus is used copy fault status from one row of cores to 
    other rows of similar cores on a chip.

    create_bridge_delay_tests:
      
    create_bridge_delay_tests is used to target delay bridge faults for 
    test generation.

    create_bridge_tests:
      
    create_bridge_tests is used to target static bridge faults for test generation.

    create_burnin_tests:
      
    create_burnin_tests is used to create burn-in tests with a user-supplied pattern 
    for the device under test.

    create_cell_exhaustive:
      
    create_cell_exhaustive command is used to create Cell Exhaustive Pattern Faults for combinatorial
    blocks.

    create_gate_exhaustive:
      
    create_gate_exhaustive command is used to create Gate Exhaustive Pattern Faults for combinatorial
    primitive blocks.

    create_diag_tests_logic_mask:
      
    create_diag_tests_logic_mask command observes/masks all the specified channels in the logic 
    patterns in the input experiment. 

    create_diag_tests_scanchain_mask:
      
     create_diag_tests_scanchain_mask command is used to generate special scan mask
     patterns to observe one channel per test sequence.

    create_diag_tests_scanchain_xorsegments:
      
    create_diag_tests_scanchain_xorsegments is used for the creation of test patterns
    that allow on-tester scan chain diagnosis by leveraging the XOR gates.

    create_diagnostics_dashboard:
      
    create_diagnostics_dashboard is used to provide a set of information that 
    can be used to get a rough estimate of how diagnostics will run on a design. 
    It is intended to be used by Cadence AE's in specific situations.

    create_embedded_test:
      
     create_embedded_test is used for pattern generation and configuration for 
     memory built-in self test (MBIST) 

    create_flow:
      
    create_flow command is used to create a flow. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    create_flow_step:
      
    create_flow_step command is used to create a flow step. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    create_iddq_tests:
      
    create_iddq_tests is used to create tests that can be used to check for 
    excessive current drain in the quiescent state of a CMOS device. 

    create_interconnect_tests:
      
    create_interconnect_tests is used to generate stuck driver tests and 
    shorted nets tests for the interconnection wiring on higher level 
    packages (e.g. MCM, cards, boards). 

    create_iowrap_delay_tests:
      
    create_iowrap_delay_tests is used to generate dynamic iowrap tests. 

    create_iowrap_tests:
      
    create_iowrap_tests is used to create stuck driver tests and 
    shorted nets tests for the uncontacted, bi-directional data pins of the 
    device under test.

    create_layout_abstractions:
      
    create_layout_abstractions is used to extract net adjacency information and 
    possible subnet groups from the physical data of the design

    create_lbist_diag_tests:
      
    create_lbist_diag_tests is used to generate the modified LBIST patterns to take to 
    simulations/tester as per user specifications. The user specify the interval and setup
    in which LBIST will unload the MISR signatures. The default setup or 1st phase unloads the
    MISR signatures after every interval. The diagnostics process requires the MISR signatures
    to be recorded after every interval. Thus miscompares recorded in this setup (1st phase) 
    is used for diagnostics purpose.
    There are other setups or phases (2nd and 3rd) in which MISR signatures will be unloaded
    after group of intervals passed away. These are used to debug patterns, if tests from 1st
    phase does not passed during simulations.
    It also runs write_vectors for new modified patterns created during various setups
    or phases.

    create_lbist_tests:
      
    create_lbist_tests is used to simulate user specified LBIST test 
    sequences.

    create_logic_delay_tests:
      
    create_logic_delay_tests is used to generate delay tests 
    with or without actual timings. 

    create_logic_smalldelay_tests:
      
    create_logic_smalldelay_tests is used to generate delay tests 
    with timings.  Tests are generated along long timing paths for faults  
    where small delay defects may impact quality.
    create_logic_tests:
      
    create_logic_tests is used to create stored pattern logic tests for
    the device under test.

    create_macro_mpr_tests:
      
    create_macro_mpr_tests is used to map existing test vectors for an
    embedded macro/core to the device under test. The vectors are defined in 
    a Macro Pattern Rule. 

    create_macro_tests:
      
    create_macro_tests is used to map existing test vectors for an embedded
    IP macro to the device under test. The vectors to be mapped must have been 
    previously converted with convert_vectors_for_macro_tests.

    create_memory_delay_tests:
      
    create_memory_delay_tests is used to generate delay tests for faults that surround 
    memories by writing thru the memory.  Another term for these tests is ram sequential. 

    create_memory_path_delay_tests:
      
    create_memory_path_delay_tests generates path tests for paths that feed or are fed by memories. 
    The memories must adhere to the Modus memory modeling requirements. 

    create_parametric_tests:
      
    create_parametric_tests is used to create parametric tests that target 
    the device drivers and receivers. 

    create_path_delay_tests:
      
    create_path_delay_tests is used to generate delay tests for specific 
    user defined logical paths that cross combinational logic.  These paths 
    may be generated with or without actual timing data from the delay model.

    create_random_tests:
      
    create_random_tests is used to generate and simulate random patterns. 

    create_retention_tests:
      
    create_retention_tests is used to create tests for state retention 
    power gating (SRPG) instances active in the test mode. 

    create_scanchain_tests:
      
    create_scanchain_tests is used to create scan tests 
    for the device under test.

    create_testmodes:
      
  create_testmodes command is used to build multiple testmodes. 
  This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    create_sequential_tests:
      
    create_sequential_tests is used to create logic tests for sequential  
    logic.  If you have sequential logic, it is recommended that this command 
    be run after create_logic_tests has marked off faults in logic without 
    deep sequentiality. 

    create_wrp_tests:
      
    create_wrp_tests is used to generate weighted random pattern tests. 

    define_attribute:
      
  define_attribute command is used to define a new attribute in get_db/set_db. 
  This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    define_proc:
      
  define_proc command is used to define a Tcl proc that used an extended argument syntax to check for legal 
  argument names and legal values. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    define_testmode:
      
  define_testmode command is used to define a flow setup and specification for build testmodes.
  This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    delete_alternate_faultmodel:
      
    delete_alternate_faultmodel is used to remove the specified alternate 
    fault model.

    delete_analyze_paths_db:
      
    delete_analyze_paths_db command is used to delete the analyze_paths database created by create_path_delay_tests command.

    delete_attribute_definition:
      
  delete_attribute_definition command is used to delete the user defined attribute in get_db/set_db. 
  This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    delete_callout:
      
    delete_callout is used to remove the specified diagnostics callout file.

    delete_chain_diagnosability:
      
    delete_chain_diagnosability is used to remove all the database created by 
    analyze_chain_diagnosability. 

    delete_committed_tests:
      
    delete_committed_tests is used to remove all committed vectors and reset 
    the fault status for the specified test mode. 

    delete_custom_circuit_state:
      
  delete_custom_circuit_state command deletes the state information which was saved through save_custom_circuit_state. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    delete_diag_ignore_faults_db:
      
     delete_diag_ignore_faults_db command is used to delete the ignored fault database
     created by prepare_diag_ignore_faults_db command.

    delete_diagnostics_db:
      
    delete_diagnostics_db is used to delete the database created by the 'prepare_diagnostics_db' 
    command. 

    delete_failset:
      
    delete_failset is used to remove the specified failset.

    delete_faultmodel:
      
    delete_faultmodel is used to remove a fault model and all other data 
    that was created using that fault model.  Logs and other user files 
    are not deleted. 

    delete_faultmodel_analysis_data:
      
    delete_faultmodel_analysis_data deletes register array and random resistant 
    analysis data created by build_faultmodel or prepare_faultmodel_analysis.

    delete_fca_database:
      
    delete_fca_database command is used to delete fault database for static and dynamic faults.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    delete_flow:
      
    delete_flow command is used to delete a flow. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    delete_flow_step:
      
    delete_flow_step command is used to delete a flow step. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    delete_ignoremeasures:
      
    delete_ignoremeasures command is used to delete previous ignore measures. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    delete_layout_abstractions:
      
    delete_layout_abstractions is used to delete the netpairs and subnet data present 
    in Modus database.

    delete_model:
      
    delete_model is used to remove a model and all other data that 
    was created using that model.  Logs and other user files are not deleted. 

    delete_sdtsnt_objectives:
      
    delete_sdtsnt_objectives is used to remove an objective model and all 
    other data that was created using that objective model.  Logs and other 
    user files are not deleted. 

    delete_shared_memory:
      
    delete_shared_memory is used to close the shared memory and semaphores created by 
    the Modus application that use Shared Memory to load design information. 

    delete_status:
      
    delete_status is used to delete the global data status records.

    delete_testmode:
      
    delete_testmode is used to remove all data associated with 
    the specified testmode from the working directory. 

    delete_testrange:
      
    delete_testrange is used to remove a range of tests from the specified 
    input uncommitted experiment. 

    delete_tests:
      
    delete_tests is used to remove all data associated with 
    the specified uncommitted experiment(s) from the working directory. 

    delete_verify_test_structures_data:
      
    delete_verify_test_structures_data is used to remove all the program data
    that was created for interactive analysis of TSV messages for this testmode.

    diagnose_failset_logic:
      
    diagnose_failset_logic is used to perform diagnostics simulation and 
    isolate the fault(s) that could explain the logic failures.  The fault 
    isolation report is called a callout. 

    diagnose_failset_scanchain:
      
    diagnose_failset_scanchain is used to perform diagnostics simulation 
    and isolate the fault(s) that could explain failures in the scan chains. 
    A callout report is produced identifying the possible defect locations 
    along the faulty scan chains. 

    diagnose_failset_scanchain_xorsegments:
      
    diagnose_failset_scanchain_xorsegments is used to process failures from the special XOR
    segment tests and isolate the fault(s) that could explain failures in the scan chains.
    A callout report is produced identifying the possible defect locations 
    along the faulty scan chains. 

    diagnose_failures:
      
    diagnose_failures is used to perform precision diagnostics on a specified set 
    of failure data from the tester. It analyzes the failure data and does scan 
    chain and/or logic diagnostics to identify faults that best explain the failures. 

    diagnose_scanchain_nofails:
      
    diagnose_scanchain_nofails is used to generate the upperbound for the scanchain 
    defect based on the specified bestguess and the testrange specification.

    diagnose_volume_failures:
      
    diagnose_volume_failures is used to perform volume diagnostics on the tester
    failure data included in the specified fail data directory. This single command 
    performs all the steps required for volume diagnostics. 

    edit_model:
      
    edit_model is used to edit the logic model.

    edit_flow:
      
    edit_flow command is used to edit flow steps. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    estimate_coverage:
      
    estimate_coverage estimates the static fault coverage for a design. 

    estimate_delay_coverage:
      
    estimate_delay_coverage estimates the dynamic fault coverage for a design. 

    expand_vectors:
      
    expand_vectors is used to expand the scan loads and unloads.  It creates a 
    TBDbin with an additional qualifier, EXPANDSCAN in the part directory. 

    extract_cellaware_defects:
      
  extract_cellaware_defects is used in the cell aware fault modeling flow to extract 
  candidate defects in standard digital library cells for subsequent characterization 
  and fault modeling. 

    find_messages:
      
    find_messages command is used to find list of messages encountered from a specified log file.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    find_message_instances:
      
    find_message_instances command is used to find instances of a specified message id from a specified log file.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    find_path:
      
     find_path command is used to perform circuit path analysis. Once you determine
     the boundaries of the path you wish to analyze, type the beginning point as "fromPin",
     then type the end point as "toPin". "show_gui" option will show the path on the current
     schematic display. "probe" option causes all the nets included in the displayed path
     to be probed in the currently selected probe color.

    get_count:
      
    get_count command is used to get count of the netlist/testmode objects. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    get_context:
      
    get_context is used to get the analysis context in the Tcl environment.
    This command can be invoked after the analysis context information is set by 
    the set_context command. This is an interactive command available only in
    the Tcl environment.

    get_coremigrationpath:
      
     get_coremigrationpath command is used to retrieve the value set by set_coremigrationpath command
     from the design database.

    get_db:
      
    get_db command is a simplified database access command to query design and testmode
    information. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    get_metric:
      
    get_metric command is used to access the metrics populated by prepare_metrics_summary command.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    get_name:
      
    get_name command is used to get name of the netlist/testmode objects. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    get_name_style:
      
    get_name_style command is used to get the current naming style. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    get_object:
      
    get_object command is used to get netlist/testmode specific dual-ported objects. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    get_openaccess_name:
      
    get_openaccess_name command is used to convert the Modus name into OpenAccess name.
    The OpenAccess name is the verilog naming style used by the commands that access
    OpenAccess physical database. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl
    environment.

    get_option:
      
    get_option command is used to retrieve the value of option set using set_option command. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    grant_access:
      
    grant_access is used to create/modify access authorization to a secured 
    database (tbdata).  Access is authorized for a specified 
    password and can be optionally limited to a specified list or set of  
    commands, a user, license host, internet address and expiration date/time. 

    graph_sdql:
      
    graph_sdql is used to graphically represent the SDQL effectiveness computed 
    by report_sdql.  

    gui_close:
      
  gui_close command is used to close Modus GUI from Tcl console. 
  This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_close_callout_viewer:
      
    gui_close_callout_viewer command is used to close GUI Callout Viewer Window. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_close_context:
      
  gui_close_context command is used to close analysis context window from Tcl console. 
  This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_close_design_browser:
      
    gui_close_design_browser command is used to close GUI Design Browser Window. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_close_hotspot_viewer:
      
  gui_close_hotspot_viewer command closes the hotspot viewer. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_close_schematic:
      
    gui_close_schematic command is used to close the schematic. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_open:
      
  gui_open command is used to open Modus GUI from Tcl console. 
  This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_open_callout_viewer:
      
    gui_open_callout_viewer  command is used to open GUI Callout Viewer Window. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_open_context:
      
  gui_open_context command is used to open analysis context window from Tcl console. 
  This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_open_design_browser:
      
    gui_open_design_browser  command is used to open GUI Design Browser Window. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_open_schematic:
      
    gui_open_schematic command is used to open the schematic. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    gui_open_snapshot:
      
    gui_open_snapshot command is used to open the snapshot in the schematic.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_probe_nets:
      
    gui_probe_nets command is used to probe the net objects in the schematic. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment. 

    gui_raise_callout_viewer:
      
    gui_raise_callout_viewer command is used to raise hidden instance of Callout Viewer GUI. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_register_highlight_script:
      
    gui_register_highlight_script command is used to specify a script to be 
    executed whenever a schematic object is highlighted. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    gui_remove_objects:
      
    gui_remove_objects command is used to remove objects from the schematic. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    gui_restore_tracing_options:
      
    gui_restore_tracing_options command is used to restore the saved trace and path
    options by gui_save_tracing_options command in Circuit Tracing Options window.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_save_snapshot:
      
    gui_save_snapshot command is used to save the snapshot in the schematic.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_save_tracing_options:
      
    gui_save_tracing_options command is used to save the existing trace and path options in the Circuit Tracing Options window.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_set_probe_color:
      
    gui_set_probe_color command is used to specify a probe color to be set in the schematic. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment. 

    gui_unprobe_nets:
      
    gui_unprobe_nets command is used to unprobe the probed net objects in the schematic. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment. 

    gui_unregister_highlight_script:
      
    gui_unregister_highlight_script command is used to remove a registered 
    highlight script. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_view_help:
      
    gui_view_help command is used to open the GUI Help Window. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_view_hotspots:
      
    gui_view_hotspots command is used to open hotspot GUI.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_view_info:
      
    gui_view_info command is used to specify a string to be displayed in the schematic.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_view_objects:
      
    gui_view_objects command is used to view objects in schematic. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    gui_view_pmbist_scheduler:
      
    gui_view_pmbist_scheduler command is used to create customized schedule for memory testing 
    during programmable memory built-in self test (PMBIST). This is an interactive command available 
    only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_view_trace:
      
    gui_view_trace command is used to view the callout location in the schematic 
    and to visualize the path from callout location to capture flops. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment. 

    gui_view_trace_color_reset:
      
    gui_view_trace_color_reset command is used to reset the pin and fault color from schematic
    view, that are due to gui_view_trace command.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_view_trace_set_tracing_options:
      
    gui_view_trace_set_tracing_options command is used to reset the trace and path options in
    Circuit Tracing Options window. It is required for the working of the gui_view_trace command.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_view_tracing_options:
      
    gui_view_tracing_options command is used to view tracing window that is present in the schematic.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    gui_view_tsv_summary:
      
    gui_view_tsv_summary command is used to view summary window for all the TSV messages 
    in the design. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    gui_view_tsv_violation:
      
    gui_view_tsv_violation command is used to view TSV violation in the GUI Schematic 
    window. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    help:
      
    help is used to get information on the available Modus commands.
    help with no options prints all the verbs that are used as the first word
    of the commands, with a brief description.  help with a string prints all
    commands that contain that string. help all prints all commands. 

    help_option:
      
    help_option command is used to view help of the available options for the commands. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    init_flow:
      
    init_flow command is used to setup the environment for running flowkit. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    insert_vector_pipeline_sequence:
      
    insert_vector_pipeline_sequence is used to alter test vectors to take 
    the pipeline depth, specified in the test mode, into consideration.

    is_attribute:
      
    is_attribute command is used to check whether an attribute exists or not.  
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    is_flow:
      
    is_flow command is used to check what flow or flow steps have been run. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    killit:
      
    killit is used to kill any existing Modus GUI processes that are
    running on the current machine under your userid.  This is not the 
    recommended method of ending Modus (using Exit is recommended).  However, 
    if the GUI is not responding for some reason, killit may be used to 
    terminate it. 

    migrate_core_tests:
      
    migrate_core_tests is used to map existing test vectors for an embedded
    IP core to the device under test. The vectors to be mapped must have been 
    previously converted with prepare_core_migration_tests.

    migrate_pdl_tests:
      
    migrate_pdl_tests is used to map existing test vectors for an
    embedded macro/core to the device under test. The vectors are defined in 
    a PDL file. 

    msgHelp:
      
    msgHelp is used to get extended help on a Cadence message. 
    To get help enter: msgHelp <message id> (for example, msgHelp TSV-014). 
    This is the same information that prints in the GUI session log when you 
    click on a message in the GUI Log browser.

    prepare_cloak_password:
      
    prepare_cloak_password is used to generate a time sensitive encrypted
    password to be used to uncloak a cell in the hierarchical model that
    has a TB_cloak_password attribute.

    prepare_clock_constraints:
      
    prepare_core_migration_diagnostics:
      
    prepare_core_migration_diagnostics is used to prepare the data associated 
    with a stand-alone IP core for use in diagnostics processing when the core 
    is embedded in another device.

    prepare_core_migration_data:
      
    prepare_core_migration_data is used to perform three migration steps. 
        1. Prepare Core testmode information for migration 
        2. Prepare fault data for migration 
        3. Prepare test data for migration 

    prepare_core_migration_faults:
      
    prepare_core_migration_faults is used to create the core fault rule file 
    to be used when building the chip-level fault model for Hierarchical Test.

    prepare_core_migration_info:
      
    prepare_core_migration_info is used to create the out-of-context core migration
    information file.

    prepare_core_migration_tests:
      
    prepare_core_migration_tests is used to convert vectors for an IP core 
    to the format required for creating chip tests for the SoC when the core 
    is embedded in another device. 

    prepare_cpf_data:
      
    prepare_cpf_data reads in a CPF file, which may source other CPF files, and 
    verifies it against the Modus model. This command must be run prior to executing 
    other Modus commands that use the CPF information. 
    It is obsolete now. It will not be available from 18.1 release. Please use 
    read_power_intent command with option 'format' set to 'cpf'. 

    prepare_derived_failset:
      
    prepare_derived_failset is used to map failure data to a derived failset.

    prepare_detected_faults:
      
    prepare_detected_faults is used to create a fault rule file for the cell 
    that identifies faults that should be marked detected when this cell is 
    used on a higher level package.  
    This is used when the patterns for the cell (e.g., chip) are to be 
    reapplied on the higher level package (e.g., SCM). 

    prepare_device_failure_groups:
      
    prepare_device_failure_groups is used to group failures of multiple devices in efficient groups/buckets 
    which will give optimum performance gain with MDD(Multiple Device Diagnostics) method.

    prepare_diag_ignore_faults_db:
      
     prepare_diag_ignore_faults_db command is used to identify hyper-active faults which are
     dropped (reason 'activity') by simulator during fault simulation. The hyper-active faults
     generally increases the fault simulation time in logic diagnosis. Once you determine
     the hyper-active faults, you can eliminate the hyper-active faults from the list of faults
     selected for fault simulation during logic diagnosis command run.

    prepare_domain_constraints:
      
     prepare_domain_constraints is used to identify clock domains that interact.
     Clock domains may be primary inputs, PPIs, internal domains identified during
     build_testmode, or any other internal pin (specified via the inclockfile.)
     Domains that interact will be protected via falsepath constraints during 
     Test Generation and Simulation.

     prepare_domain_constraints also creates a domain pairs file that lists the 
     domains pairs that interact and indicates whether they are properly fenced by 
     a block_inputs type internal domain register. Domains that are not properly fenced 
     but are allowed to interact may be identified by marking the domains as SAFE in 
     the domain pairs file and reading it back into prepare_domain_constraints.
     Refer the OPCG definition section of build_testmode in the Modeling Reference for 
     more information on block_inputs registers.

    prepare_diagnostics_db:
      
    prepare_diagnostics_db traces through all clock, control signals and records the nodes 
    traversed into the database, whose name is specified along with the command. Along with 
    each node, the scan flip flops to which the respective node reaches when traced forward 
    is also recorded. 

    prepare_failset_partition:
      
    prepare_failset_partition is used to prepare a failset from a cone 
    trace.

    prepare_diagnostics_setup:
      
    prepare_diagnostics_setup generates input files for injecting logic faults and scan chain faults 
    in the design and writes out scripts to do the fault injection. 

    prepare_fault_subset:
      
    prepare_fault_subset allows you to specify a subset of faults to be 
    included in an experiment.  It also allows you to adjust the fault status.
    The resulting experiment is used as input to create tests that target 
    the specified faults; or ignore the faults with adjusted status. 

    prepare_faultmodel_analysis:
      
    prepare_faultmodel_analysis is used to prepare fault analysis information 
    that will be used during Stored Pattern Test Generation. 

    prepare_fca_database:
      
    prepare_fca_database command is used to prepare fault database for static and dynamic faults.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    prepare_hotspot_db:
      
    prepare_hotspot_db command is used to create database from HIF file.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    prepare_ht_diagnostics_workdirs:
      
    prepare_ht_diagnostics_workdirs command is used to set up chip database and respective core databases. 

    prepare_ht_failures:
      
  prepare_ht_failures generates core wise failures for Hierarchical Test Diagnostics.

    prepare_ignore_faults:
      
    prepare_ignore_faults is used to create a fault rule file for the cell 
    that identifies the faults that should be ignored when this cell is 
    used on a higher level package. 

    prepare_memory_failset:
      
     prepare_memory_failset accepts one or more fail data set (FDS) failure logs
     and a pointer to the manufacturing memory test database. With the interface
     files and patterns in their defined locations, all FDS data is processed
     through FDSlog2CPP and analyze_embedded_test to populate the balance of the
     database for use by the visualization software.  Patterns must have been 
     created by create_embedded_test using the 'testblockname' option. 

    prepare_memory_fault_subset:
      
    prepare_memory_fault_subset is to build a fault subset of only memory faults that are 
    to be included in an experiment. 

    prepare_memory_path_delay:
      
    prepare_memory_path_delay generates a path fault model for paths that feed or are fed by memories. 
    The memories must adhere to the Modus memory modeling requirements. 

    prepare_memory_sequences:
      
    prepare_memory_sequences generates test sequences that may be used to test memory faults. 
    The memories that the sequences are generated for must adhere to the Modus memory modeling requirements. 

    prepare_metrics_summary:
      
    prepare_metrics_summary command creates a snapshot of Metrics for the runs done till the point of execution of this command.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    prepare_opcg_input:
      
  prepare_opcg_input command is used to define cut points and PPIs for at-speed testmodes. 
  It finds PLLs, go-synch gating logic, and deskewers and their associated control latches. 
  It uses all this information to edit the mode definition file 
  and the sequence definition file for the ASST testmode. 

    prepare_opcg_test_sequences:
      
    prepare_opcg_test_sequences is used to generate test sequences for
    OPCG test modes when the OPCG logic is inserted by Cadence RTL Compiler
    or Genus. It currently can generate intra-domain, inter-domain and 
    static sequences.

    prepare_path_delay:
      
    prepare_path_delay is used to prepare the design for 
    create_path_delay_tests. 

    prepare_pipeline_sequence:
      
    prepare_pipeline_sequence is used to prepare pipeline and circuit state 
    information to be used by create_logic_tests.  

    prepare_ra_faultsubset:
      
    prepare_ra_faultsubset allows you to specify a subset of faults to be 
    included in an experiment.  It also allows you to adjust the fault status.
    The resulting experiment is used as input to create tests that target 
    the specified faults; or ignore the faults with adjusted status. 

    prepare_sequence_templates:
      
    prepare_sequence_templates is used to create test sequence templates for 
    create_logic_delay_tests. 

    prepare_timed_sequences:
      
    prepare_timed_sequences is used to prepare the design for create_logic_delay_tests. 

    prepare_vectors_for_conversion:
      
    prepare_vectors_for_conversion is intended only for use in specially written 
    application commands/scripts for specific conversion flows. It converts vectors 
    into a format that is ready for conversion. The format, that is similar to the  
    structure neutral format, uses Load_SR/Unload_SR events in place of Scan_Load/  
    Scan_Unload events. 

    read_bsdl:
      
    read_bsdl is used to read and syntax check boundary scan design language

    read_failures:
      
    read_failures is used to read the tester failure data into 
    binary format.  The data in this format is referred to as a failset.

    read_icl:
      
    read_icl is used to read an ICL file and generate the isolation data for 
    IJTAG patterns retargeting.

    read_layout_abstractions:
      
    read_layout_abstractions is used to read the netpairs and subnet data into the 
    Modus database. This information is used for further processing in 
    diagnostics.

    read_power_intent:
      
    read_power_intent reads in a UPF/1801 file or CPF file, which may source 
    other UPF/1801 files or CPF files respectively, and verifies it against 
    the Modus model. This command must be run prior to executing other Modus 
    commands that use power intent information(UPF/1801 or CPF). 

    read_sdc:
      
    read_sdc is used to read and verify design constraints from an SDC 
    (Synopsys Design Constraint) file 

    read_sdf:
      
    read_sdf is used to create a delay model from an 
    SDF (Standard Delay Format) file. 

    read_sequence_definition:
      
    read_sequence_definition is used to read a user supplied sequence for 
    use by a Cadence Test application. 

    read_vectors:
      
    read_vectors is used to read vectors, written in the specified language, 
    into binary format for subsequent processing.

    redirect:
      
    redirect command is used to redirect std output to a user specified file or Tcl variable. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    register_alternate_faultmodel:
      
    register_alternate_faultmodel command register alternate fault model binary file 'faultModel.<ALTFAULT>' 
    in globalData. The user has to copy the binary file in tbdata before running this command. 

    remove_domain_constraints:
      
     remove_domain_constraints is used to remove the constraints  
     identified by prepare_domain_constraints for clock domains that interact.

    remove_sdc:
      
    remove_sdc is used to remove existing design constraints that may be 
    registered in the circuit model.

    report_callout:
      
    report_callout generates a callout report.

    report_chains:
      
    report_chains command is used to report the information about the scan chains 
    in the design. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    report_clock_gates:
      
    report_clock_gates command is used to report the clock gate information for lowpower parts 

    report_cluster_info:
      
    report_cluster_info is used to report cluster, region and hard to control/observe
    nets associated with an experiment created by analyze_lbist_testpoints. 

    report_context:
      
    report_context command is used to report the current context in tcl environment. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    report_diag_scanchain_xorsegments:
      
    report_diag_scanchain_xorsegments is used to report all the XOR segments identified
    through generation of the special XOR patterns by create_diag_tests_scanchain_xorsegments.

    report_domain_fault_statistics:
      
     report_domain_fault_statistics is used to print out the fault coverage 
     statistics for a clock domain.

    report_domain_faults:
      
     report_domain_faults is used to print out a list of faults for a clock 
     domain that meet the specified criteria.

    report_fault_effects:
      
    report_fault_effects is used to perform simulation on the specified 
    list of faults and reports the fault effects. 

    report_fault_statistics:
      
    report_fault_statistics is used to print out the fault coverage 
    statistics.

    report_faults:
      
    report_faults is used to print out a list of faults that meet the specified 
    criteria. 

    report_flow:
      
    report_flow command is used to report the flow statistics. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    report_good_machine_states:
      
    report_good_machine_states is used to perform good machine simulation on the specified 
    list of sequences and report simulated values on the user specified set of nodes. 

    report_groups_for_macro_tests:
      
    report_groups_for_macro_tests is used to print out the grouping information
    for macro tests.  The grouping is determined by verify_macro_isolation 

    report_instances:
      
    report_instances command is used to report the information about the specified 
    instances. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    report_memory_fault_statistics:
      
    report_memory_fault_statistics reports the fault statistics for individual memories.  
    The memories must adhere to the Modus memory modeling requirements. 

    report_messages:
      
  report_messages command is used to report all types of messages (info,warning,severe_warning,error) for the command. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    report_metric:
      
    report_metric command is used to create a webpage for the populated Metrics.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    report_miscompare_database:
      
    report_miscompare_database command is used to report the contents of miscompare database. 
     This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    report_model_statistics:
      
    report_model_statistics is used to print out information about the 
    Cadence Test logic model. 

    report_odometer:
      
    report_odometer is used to report details of an odometer.  
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    report_pathfault_statistics:
      
    report_pathfault_statistics is used to print out the path coverage 
    statistics resulting from path delay test generation. 

    report_pathfaults:
      
    report_pathfaults is used to print out individual path fault status 
    resulting from path delay test generation. 

    report_physical_coordinates_for_instance:
      
    report_physical_coordinates_for_instance command is used to report all X-Y coordinates of
    an instance box in OpenAccess physical database. This is an interactive command available
    only in the Tcl environment.

    report_physical_correlation:
      
    report_physical_correlation is used to generate a report which indicates
    the degree of correlation between the nets and blocks (instances of technology
    cells), in the Modus logic model and a corresponding physical design
    in an OpenAccess database. 

    report_physical_diagnostics_setup:
      
    report_physical_diagnostics_setup command is used to report all the options that are used
    to access OpenAccess physical database. This is an interactive command available only in the
    Tcl environment.

    report_physical_instance_from_coordinates:
      
    report_physical_instance_from_coordinates command is used to report all the instances that are on
    the given X-Y coordinate in OpenAccess physical database. The command might return multiple instances
    in case more than one instance is present at the same location. This is an interactive command 
    available only in the Tcl environment.

    report_physical_objects_from_coordinates:
      
    report_physical_objects_from_coordinates command is used to report all the objects such as
    shapes or pins present at a given X-Y coordinate in OpenAccess physical database. This is
    an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    report_physical_trends:
      
    report_physical_trends is used to report the physical diagnostics trends for 
    the specified nets of interest.

    report_pins:
      
    report_pins command is used to report the information about the specified pins.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment and operates
    on the context set using set_context command.

    report_processing_status:
      
    report_processing_status is used to print out the status of the process 
    audits.

    report_running_commands:
      
    report_running_commands command is used to report currenty running processes running in the Modus 
    Tcl console. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    report_scan_flop_fault_effects:
      
    report_scan_flop_fault_effects is used to perform simulation on the specified 
    list of scan flop faults and reports the fault effects. 

    report_scanchain_holes:
      
    report_scanchains:
      
    report_scanchains is used to perform the tracing and reporting of scan path 
    for the specified scan chain(s).

    report_scandiag_dictionary:
      
    report_scandiag_dictionary is used to report the information stored in the scan 
    chain diagnostics dictionary files generated by analyze_chain_diagnosability.

    report_sdc:
      
     report_sdc is used to report the design constraints that were processed by the read_sdc command 
     from an SDC (Synopsys(R) Design Constraint) file.

    report_sdql:
      
    report_sdql is used to calculate the SDQL effectiveness of a set of test patterns.

    report_sdtsnt_objective_statistics:
      
    report_sdtsnt_objective_statistics is used to print out the coverage 
    statistics resulting from stuck driver and shorted nets tests. 

    report_sdtsnt_objectives:
      
    report_sdtsnt_objectives is used to print out the objectives used for 
    stuck driver and/or shorted nets tests. 

    report_sequences:
      
    report_sequences is used to print out the binary sequence 
    definition file in ascii format. 

    report_simulation_values:
      
    report_simulation_values command is used to report values on a list of pins/nodes while simulating 
    a sequence or an event. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    report_test_structures:
      
    report_test_structures is used to print out information about the test 
    structures in the logic model as configured for the specified test mode; 
    such as, information about the scan chains. 

    report_testfunctions:
      
    report_testfunctions command is used to report the information about the pins 
    associated with the specified test function names. This is an interactive command 
    available only in the Tcl environment and operates on the context set using 
    set_context command.

    report_tester_description_rule:
      
    report_tester_description_rule is used to print the TDR (Tester Description
    Rule) data. 

    report_tsv_messages:
      
    report_tsv_messages command is used to report all the TSV messages 
    in the design. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    report_vector_simulation_options:
      
    report_vector_simulation_options is used to print the simulation options 
    that were in effect when the vectors were created. 

    report_vector_statistics:
      
    report_vector_statistics is used to print out a summary that includes the 
    count of each hierarchical level of the vectors. 

    report_vector_summary:
      
     report_vector_summary is used to print a summary of each type of vector 
     created and their effectiveness in detecting faults. 

    report_vector_volume:
      
    report_vector_volume is used to calculate the test data volume based on 
    test pattern statistics.  It also estimates whether the data will fit in 
    the tester buffer. 

    report_vectors:
      
    report_vectors is used to print out the binary vectors in 
    ascii format. 

    report_vectors_for_core_migration_tests:
      
    report_vectors_for_core_migration_tests is used to print out the binary vectors, 
    that are intended for test data migration, in ascii format. 

    report_vectors_for_macro_tests:
      
    report_vectors_for_macro_tests is used to print out the binary vectors, 
    that are intended for test data migration, in ascii format. 

    report_verify_test_structures_messages:
      
    report_verify_test_structures_messages is used to print out the messages 
    resulting from a previous invocation of verify_test_structures.

    report_volume_database_info:
      
       ================report_volume_database_info=================
      USAGE:- report_volume_database_info WORKDIR=<WORKDIR>        
      This command reports Volume Diagnostics Database Details     
      It reports the following details:-                           
      a. Whether the specified WORKDIR is connected to Volume Diagnostics Database Directory 
      b. If it is connected to Volume Database Directory:-
            Reports Database connection Details
            If server for the specified database is up and running
              If so, it reports all the databases
      ============================================================

    reset_find_path_options:
      
  reset_find_path_options command resets find_path options. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    reset_trace_options:
      
    reset_trace_options command is used to reset the trace values in Tcl as well GUI provided GUI is opened.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    restore_custom_circuit_state:
      
  restore_custom_circuit_state command restores the circuit state which was previously saved or returned through save_custom_circuit_state. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    run_meth_batch:
      
    run_meth_batch is used to run a methodology in a batch environment. 
    This command is available only in the modus Tcl environment. 

    run_flow:
      
    run_flow command is used to run the flowkit. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    save_custom_circuit_state:
      
  save_custom_circuit_state command saves the state information of entire design in Modus database. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    schedule_flow:
      
    schedule_flow command is used to schedule a flow for subsequent execution. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    set_context:
      
    set_context is used to set or clear the analysis context in the Tcl environment.
    This command should be invoked after the project is successfully set by
    set_db workdir command.  To get the context information set by this command,
    use get_context command.This is an interactive command available only in
    the Tcl environment.

    set_coremigrationpath:
      
     set_coremigrationpath command is used to save the 'coremigratepath' in the design database.

    set_db:
      
    set_db command is used to set or update editable attributes.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    set_flowkit_read_db_args:
      
    set_flowkit_read_db_args command is used to set options for read_db when running the flow. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    set_flowkit_write_db_args:
      
    set_flowkit_write_db_args command is used to set options for write_db when running the flow. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    set_name_style:
      
    set_name_style command is used to set naming style to synthesis or test. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    set_option:
      
    set_option command is used to set the option values for the commands. 
    To get the value set by this command, use get_option command.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    set_prefix_netlist_object_name:
      
    set_prefix_netlist_object_name command is used to set user defined prefixes
    for netlist names (pins, blocks and nets) in Tcl and GUI.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    setup_volume_database:
      
    setup_volume_database is used to set up the Volume Diagnostics Database 
    infrastructure for the specified design on the specified database (which is 
    accessed by a running server started with start_volume_server). 

    simulate_state:
      
    simulate_state command is used to set or reset the circuit state. This command
    should be invoked after setting a valid testmode using set_context command.
    To check the state set by this command, you can do 'get_db circuit_state'.
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    simulate_test_data:
      
    simulate_test_data command is used to simulate a sequence. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    simulate_value:
      
    simulate_value command is used to simulate value for the specified pin. 
    The values affected by this command are updated on pin objects. To 
    check the value on a pin object, you can do get_db <pin_object> .value. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    simulate_vectors:
      
    simulate_vectors is used to simulate/fault grade manual patterns. 

    start_physical_server:
      
    start_physical_server is used to start a server process to which diagnostics 
    applications connect to fetch information needed for performing physical diagnostics.

    start_volume_server:
      
    start_volume_server is used to start a new Volume Diagnostics Database server 
    for the specified database or to restart a Volume Diagnostics Database server 
    that was stopped with stop_volume_server. 

    stop_physical_server:
      
    stop_physical_server is used to stop the physical diagnostics server
    started by start_physical_server.

    stop_volume_server:
      
    stop_volume_server is used to stop a Volume Diagnostics Database Server 
    that was previously started with command start_volume_server.

    suppress_messages:
      
  suppress_messages command disables the printing of specified messages. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    tbver:
      
     tbver is used to display the version of Modus that is  
     set up in the current environment.  This is most useful if you are 
     in the command line (modus or modus -c) environment.  The result is 
     a single line indicating the Modus version number, date and
     platform. 

    trace_circuit:
      
    trace_circuit command is used to trace the circuit in forward or backward
    direction starting from the specified pin name. To trace the circuit in a 
    specific circuit state, you will have to first invoke the simulate_state 
    command to set the state before invoking trace_circuit command. This is an 
    interactive command available only in the Tcl environment and operates on the
    context set using set_context command.

    translate_name:
      
    translate_name command is used to convert names from synthesis to test and vice-versa. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    true_time:
      
    true_time creates and runs the true time use model script based on your 
    description in the setup file. See description in the ATPG documentation. 

    unlock_db_resources:
      
    unlock_db_resources command releases all the database resources 
    acquired. This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    unset_option:
      
    unset_option command is used to unset options set using set_option command. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    vcd:
      
    vcd command is used for virtual directory navigation. This command is analogous
    to the UNIX cd command. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    verify_11491_boundary:
      
    verify_11491_boundary verifies that the device under test's boundary 
    scan structures and BSDL are compliant with the IEEE 1149.1 standard.

    verify_asst_frequencies:
      
    verify_clock_constraints:
      
    verify_clock_constraints will verify the clock constraint file data
    against the Tester Description Rule (TDR). 

    verify_ignoremeasures:
      
    verify_ignoremeasures is used to verify the names of the latches included 
    in the input ignoremeasures file. 

    verify_macro_isolation:
      
    verify_macro_isolation is used to ensure that embedded macros can be 
    isolated for testing. It also creates the isolation data for macro tests.

    verify_migration_data:
      
    verify_migration_data is used to verify the chip to core interface by simulating the test vectors 
    produced by migrate_core_tests along with the original test vectors for the embedded IP core produced 
    by prepare_core_migration_tests.

    verify_mos_states:
      
    verify_mos_states reads in a TBD tdm file and a user supplied chip level MOS pin setting file. 
    It extracts the MOS pins,states specified in the chip descripfile and also core MOS pins, states from the tdm file. 
    Then it ensures whether or not are we getting the expected states at the cores with a given chip level state. 

    verify_sequences:
      
    verify_sequences analyzes manually specified test sequences for 
    effectiveness, accuracy, and completeness.

    verify_test_structures:
      
    verify_test_structures is used to verify the logic test structures 
    on the device under test. 

    vls:
      
    vls command is used to list the current directory content and also the 
    attributes associated with the current directory. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    vpwd:
      
    vpwd command prints the present working directory. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    write_diag_ignore_faults_db:
      
     write_diag_ignore_faults_db command is used to print the list of faults (text format)
     ignored in ignored fault database.

    what_is:
      
    what_is command is used to convert netlist name to CUI object. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    write_embedded_test:
      
     write_embedded_test is used to create a simulation script for one or more experiments for 
     memory built-in self test (MBIST) patterns. 

    write_voltus:
      
    write_voltus is used to generate scripts to do the vector less or vector based
    power analysis in Voltus. 

    write_failures:
      
    write_failures writes out the failure data for the specified failset.

    write_flow:
      
    write_flow command is used to write the flow and steps. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    write_flow_template:
      
    write_flow_template command is used to create a set of template TCL files to be used as the basis for a flow. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    write_hotspots:
      
    write_hotspots command is used to generate hotspot file for user specified list of fault file by communicating with physical server.
    The command is tbdata independent and the faultfile contains fault information in terms of fault type and pin and net name.

    write_ignoremeasures:
      
    write_ignoremeasures command is used to write ignore measures in file. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment 
    and operates on the context set using set_context command.

    write_layout_abstractions:
      
    write_layout_abstractions is used to write the netpairs and subnet data associated 
    with the specified nets or pins.

    write_options:
      
    write_options command is used to write all the options set using set_option command into the specified file. 
    This is an interactive command available only in the Tcl environment.

    write_toggle_gram:
      
    write_toggle_gram is used to analyze tests (committed or uncommitted) and 
    write reports that identify sequences with excessive switching activity. 

    write_vector_correspondence:
      
    write_vector_correspondence is used to create the vector correspondence 
    file, which identifies the correspondence between vector bit positions and 
    the model pins and blocks. 

    write_vectors:
      
    write_vectors is used to write out the test vectors in the 
    specified language. 

Objects:
    root:
      Root object where global attributes are found
    design:
      Top module for the design
    port:
      Port for the design
    net:
      A wire in the design
    module:
      Verilog module for a hierarchical instance
    hinst:
      Hierarchical instance of a Verilog module in the design
    hpin:
      Hierarchical pin for a hierarchical instance
    hport:
      Hierarchical port for a hierarchical instance
    hnet:
      Hierarchical net in the design
    base_cell:
      Verilog module for an instance of a technology library cell
    inst:
      Technology library cell instance in the design
    pin:
      Pin for a technology library cell instance
    inst_hport:
      Hierarchical port within a technology library cell
    inst_hnet:
      Hierarchical net segment within a technology base cell
    hprim_cell:
      Verilog module for a non-primitive instance within a technology library cell
    hprim:
      Instance of a Verilog non-primitive within a technology library cell
    hprim_hpin:
      Pin for a Verilog non-primitive within a technology library cell
    hprim_hport:
      Hierarchical port for a Verilog non-primitive within a technology library cell
    prim_cell:
      Verilog primitive within a technology library cell
    prim:
      Instance of a Verilog primitive within a technology library cell
    prim_pin:
      Pin for a Verilog primitive within a technology library cell
    node:
      Node in the design
    fault:
      Fault in the design
    testmode:
      Testmode in the design
    test_function:
      Clocks, scan controls, etc., for controlling the test functions in the testmode
    ppi:
      Pseudo-primary-input(PPI) in the testmode
    control_chain:
      Controllable Chain in the testmode
    control_flop:
      Flop in a Controllable Chain in the testmode
    observe_chain:
      Observable Chain in the testmode
    observe_flop:
      Flop in an Observable Chain in the testmode
    opcg_domain:
      OPCG Clock Domain in the testmode
    opcg_domain_register:
      OPCG Domain Register in the OPCG Clock Domain
    opcg_domain_flop:
      OPCG Domain Flop in the OPCG Domain Register
    opcg_chain:
      OPCG Chain in the testmode
    opcg_flop:
      OPCG Flop in the OPCG Chain
    ignore_measure:
      An ignore measure object specifies an observe point for which no measure value will be created
    flow_step:
      Flow step object
    flow:
      Flow object
    correlated_control_flop:
      Correlated Control Flop
    base_pin:
      Base pins for base_cells
    module_pin:
      Modules pins for modules
    delay_model:
      Delay model in the design
    altfault:
      Alt Fault  in the design
    trace_option:
      Trace options to perform tracing in console as well as GUI
    find_path_option:
      Path options to view path in console as well as GUI
    simulation_option:
      Simulation options to perform simulation for sequences in console
    channel_mask_flop:
      Flop in a Channel Mask Chain. This Flop may also be in a Channel Mask Register
    experiment:
      Experiment in the testmode
    failset:
      Failset in the testmode and experiment
    callout:
      Callout in the failset 
    attribute:
      Attribute metadata
    obj_type:
      Object metadata
    option:
      Option object. This is used to set keywords for the application commands
    command_option:
      Command option object
    command:
      Command object
    patt_data:
      Pattern data object
    sequence:
      Sequence object
    event:
      Event object
    misr_flop:
      Multiple Input Signature Register Flops
    pattern_generator_flop:
      Pattern Generator Flops
    misr:
      Multiple Input Signature Registers
    pattern_generator:
      Pattern Generators
    fixed_value_latch:
      Fixed Value Latches in the testmode
    channel_mask_chain:
      Channel Mask Chains in the testmode
    channel_mask_register:
      Channel Mask Registers in the testmode
    opcg_pll:
      OPCG Pll in the testmode
    opcg_pll_register:
      OPCG Pll Register in the OPCG Pll
    opcg_pll_flop:
      OPCG Pll Flop in the OPCG Pll Register
    tsv_message:
      TSV Messages for the current context
    tsv_message_instance:
      TSV Message Instances for the current context
    si_to_control_chain_pipeline_flop:
      SI To Control Chain Pipeline Flop
    si_to_pattern_generator_pipeline_flop:
      SI To Pattern Generator Pipeline Flop
    pattern_generator_to_control_chain_pipeline_flop:
      Pattern Generator To Control Chain Pipeline Flop
    observe_chain_to_misr_pipeline_flop:
      Observe Chain To MISR Pipeline Flop
    observe_chain_to_so_pipeline_flop:
      Observe Chain To Scan Out Pipeline Flop
    channel_mask_enable_pipeline_flop:
      Channel Mask Enable Pipeline Flop
    low_power_gating_chain:
      Low Power Gating Chain
    low_power_gating_flop:
      Low Power Gating Flop
    model_message:
      Model Messages in the design
    model_message_instance:
      Model Message Instances in the design
    testmode_message:
      Testmode Messages in the design
    testmode_message_instance:
      Testmode Message Instances in the design
    faultmodel_message:
      Faultmodel Messages in the design
    faultmodel_message_instance:
      Faultmodel Message Instances in the design
    define_testmode_obj:
      Define testmode object
    cell:
      Cells, added for common attribute updates, returns base_cells and modules
    model_attribute:
      Model attributes in the designs
    floating_latch:
      Floating Latches in the designs
    inactive_latch:
      Inactive Latches in the designs
Attributes:
  active_core_instances(root):# Active core instance list
  advanced_keyword_search(root):# Include advanced keywords in the output
  allowflushedmeasures(root): # Allows build_testmode to identify flushed latches as observe register elements in support of gated clocks
  allowmissingmodules(root):  # Create Black Box for Missing Module Definitions
  altfault(root):             # Name of the alt fault
  blockinputs(root):          # whether to block inputs from other domains when such OPCG support logic exists
  bsdlpkgpath(root):          # The path to the standard and user defined BSDL Package file(s).
  callout(root):              # Name of the callout
  channel_mask_load_section(root):# Name of the channel mask load section that was set using simulate_state
  circuit_state(root):        # Name of the circuit state that was set using simulate_state
  clockconstraints(root):     # File Containing Clock Constraint
  cmd_file(root):             # Output file for command logging 
  combinesections(root):      # Limit the number of output files
  core_instances(root):       # core instance list In HT Design
  cpu_time(root):             # CPU time taken
  current_design(root):       # 
  default_circuit_state(root):# Include default circuit state in the output
  delay_model(root):          # Name of the delay model
  design_revision_number(root):# Design Revision Number to be stored in globalData for hotspot files.
  designsource(root):         # The list of files/directories identifying the input design source.
  designtop(root):            # Module Definition for Design Under Test
  experiment(root):           # Name of the experiment
  failset(root):              # Name of the failSet
  faultpath(root):            # The directories to be searched for fault rules.
  flow_branch(root):          # Branch being run for a hierarchical flow.
  flow_caller_data(root):     # Data used by the caller of the tool to identify this flow.
  flow_db_directory(root):    # Flow directory where results databases are stored.
  flow_error_errorinfo(root): # Tcl error stack in error database.
  flow_error_message(root):   # Tcl error message in error database.
  flow_error_write_db(root):  # Write a database when a flow step results in an error condition.
  flow_exit_when_done(root):  # Exit after running final step.
  flow_feature_values(root):  # Global feature settings.
  flow_features(root):        # Global feature definitions.
  flow_footer_tcl(root):      # TCL script to run when a flow ends.
  flow_header_tcl(root):      # TCL script to run when a flow starts.
  flow_hier_path(root):       # Path of current flow within the flow hierarchy.
  flow_history(root):         # Complete flow run history.
  flow_log_directory(root):   # Flow directory where log files are stored.
  flow_log_prefix_generator(root):# TCL script to create log filenames in Flow tool.
  flow_mail_on_error(root):   # Email to flow_mail_to if an error is detected.
  flow_mail_to(root):         # Email address where results are sent.
  flow_metrics_file(root):    # Flow metrics file for reporting results.
  flow_metrics_snapshot_parent_uuid(root):# The snapshot uuid the results from this flow will be appended to.
  flow_metrics_snapshot_uuid(root):# The snapshot uuid of the most recent flow step executed.
  flow_overwrite_db(root):    # Enables overwriting databases when saving.
  flow_plugin_names(root):    # Names of all internal plug-in points.
  flow_plugin_steps(root):    # List of plug-in steps that have been added through edit_flow.
  flow_post_db_overwrite(root):# If set within a skip_db flow_step, it allows the user to identify the name and type of database to present to future flows as the flow_starting_db.
  flow_remark(root):          # Remark from the last flow yaml file loaded.
  flow_report_directory(root):# Flow directory where reports are written.
  flow_reset_time_after_flow_init(root):# Reset all time measures after flow init.
  flow_run_tag(root):         # Tags for this particular flow run.
  flow_schedule(root):        # Set of flows to execute after the current flow completes.
  flow_starting_db(root):     # Starting database for the flow run.
  flow_startup_directory(root):# Directory where the tool was started.
  flow_status_file(root):     # File for flow status.
  flow_step_begin_tcl(root):  # Flow tcl run at the start of every step.
  flow_step_canonical_current(root):# Currently running canonical flow step.
  flow_step_check_tcl(root):  # Procedure to check the steps.
  flow_step_current(root):    # Currently running flow step.
  flow_step_end_tcl(root):    # Flow tcl run at the end of every step.
  flow_step_last(root):       # Last flow step to have been completed.
  flow_step_last_msg(root):   # Message provided for the last step that was run.
  flow_step_last_status(root):# Status for the last flow step run.
  flow_step_next(root):       # Next step to run in the flow.
  flow_summary_tcl(root):     # TCL script to run during run_flow summary.
  flow_template_feature_definition(root):# Features list and status for the current template.
  flow_template_tools(root):  # List of tools included in flow templates being run.
  flow_template_type(root):   # Type of template being run.
  flow_template_version(root):# Version of the template being run.
  flow_top(root):             # Flow to execute by default.
  flow_user_templates(root):  # Flow user template definitions.
  flow_verbose(root):         # Enable verbose flow step
  flow_working_directory(root):# Flow directory where the flow is being run.
  flow_yamllint_exec(root):   # Yamllint executable command and arguments for checking yaml files.
  flowtool_exit_timeout(root):# Maximum amount of time in seconds Flow tool will wait after a tool exits for a completed status.
  flowtool_extra_arguments(root):# Extra arguments passed to Flowtool when running in tool mode.
  flowtool_metrics_qor_excel(root):# Metrics file to write after tools exit.
  flowtool_metrics_qor_html(root):# Metrics file to write after tools exit.
  flowtool_metrics_qor_text(root):# Metrics file to write after tools exit.
  flowtool_metrics_qor_vivid(root):# Metrics file to write after tools exit.
  flowtool_predict_full_names(root):# Show skip_metric flow name in prediction.
  flowtool_summary_tcl(root): # Tcl script to run at the end of flowtool.
  free_locked_resources(root):# Resources to be released in case of locking failure
  get_db_display_limit(root): # Controls the number of objects that will be evaluated by get_db query.
  get_db_progress(root):      # True if heart-beat needs to be reported while get_db processing
  get_db_progress_iteration_count(root):# Iteration Count after which heart-beat message needs to be reported.
  gui_highlighted_object(root):# Current highlighted object in GUI
  gui_show_all_net_connections(root):# Show all possible net connections in Schematic
  includedynamic(root):       # report constraints
  includemodeinit(root):      # How to handle the modeinit sequence in the output vector files.
  interactive_message_analysis(root):# Enable Log Access
  interdomain(root):          # whether to produce interdomain tests
  intradomain(root):          # whether to produce intradomain tests
  is_design_ht(root):         # True if design is HT
  is_physical_server_online(root):# Check the Physical Server Online
  language(root):             # Specify the language in which to write vectors
  layoutviewerpath(root):     # The layout (OpenAccess Database) Path list associated with the physical design.
  log(root):                  # Customize the data included in an output log file.
  log_file(root):             # Output file for stdout logging 
  maxglobalcoveragedynamic(root):# Maximum Tested Faults (approximate) - Dynamic
  maxglobalcoveragestatic(root):#  Maximum Tested Faults (approximate) - Static
  maxpatterns(root):          # Maximum Number of Patterns
  maxscanswitching(root):     # Maximum Percentage of Switching Allowed During Scan
  message_access_testmode(root):# Allow access of testmode messages
  message_suppression(root):  # Suppress count of messages
  messagecount(root):         # Limit Messages for Specified Message Id.
  messagecounteach(root):     # Default Limit for Each Message.
  messagecounteachseverity(root):# Level of severity for which messages are to be suppressed as per messagecounteach.
  metric_advanced_url_endpoint(root):# Base URL for the advanced metric server.
  metric_capture_depth(root): # Depth for capturing hinst design and power metrics.
  metric_capture_design_image(root):# Capture design image.
  metric_capture_max_drc_markers(root):# Maximum number of DRC markers to include in metric image.
  metric_capture_min_count(root):# Minimum instance count for capturing hinst design and power metrics.
  metric_capture_overwrite(root):# Overwrite pending metrics during create_snapshot category capture.
  metric_capture_pba_tns_histogram(root):# Capture path based analysis histogram data for TNS.
  metric_capture_per_view(root):# Capture timing metrics per analysis_view.
  metric_capture_timing_path_groups(root):# Defines user path groups to capture for detailed display.
  metric_capture_timing_paths(root):# Number of paths to capture for detailed display.
  metric_capture_tns_histogram(root):# Capture histogram data for TNS.
  metric_capture_tns_histogram_buckets(root):# Number of buckets for the TNS histogram.
  metric_capture_tns_histogram_max_slack(root):# Maximum slack for the TNS histogram.
  metric_capture_tns_histogram_paths(root):# Number of paths to capture for the TNS histogram.
  metric_category_default(root):# Default metric categories to capture if none are provided.
  metric_current_run_id(root):# Current unique run ID returned by the advanced metric server.
  metric_enable(root):        # True if metrics is enabled in console
  metric_summary_metrics(root):# Summary metrics to show when creating snapshots.
  modedefpath(root):          # The path to the input Mode Definition file(s).
  name_style(root):           # The name_style that was set using set_name_style
  oacell(root):               # The cell name associated with the physical design in the OpenAccess database in which the top level design resides.
  oalib(root):                # The library name associated with the physical design in the OpenAccess database in which the top level design resides.
  oapath(root):               # The directory name associated with the physical design in the OpenAccess database.  This directory should contain a lib.defs file.
  oaview(root):               # The cell view associated with the physical design in the OpenAccess database in which the top level design resides (normally layout).
  obj_type(root):             # The object type name
  outputdir(root):            # output directory where to generate the scripts
  partial_completion(root):   # Complete partial commands and keywords
  peak_memory(root):          # Peak Memory consumption
  physical_addprefix(root):   # Prefix to be added for OA objects.
  physicalserverhost(root):   # Host machine name of physical design.
